        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Answering the Next Question Correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0) ",
          "5422 learners",
          "Assistments",
          "ITS answers",
          "Sequences of Answers",
          "Models have generally been proposed in isolation.",
          "Attempts to used Ensemble Logic to combine the predictions of different models and increase predictive performance. ",
          "Learners from assitments are treated as sequences of answers. ",
          "En-NeuralNet\nEn-RandomForest \nEn-AdaBoost-J48 \nEn-Logit  \nEn-LinReg \nEn-StepWiseReg\nPFA\nEn-AdaBoost-DecisionStumps\nBKT-EM\nBKT-LessData\nBKT-BF\nEn-Average BKT-PPS\nCGS\nCslip\nCFAR",
          "5-fold Cross-Validation",
          "Student-level aggregation: {AUC: 0.7719 - En-NeuralNet}\n\nAction-level aggregation: {AUC: 0.7693 - En-NeuralNet}",
          "Authors explain the multiple models that exist in KT and claim that ensemble approaches are relatively underexplored. For that reason, they test multiple alternatives using the Assistments Data.\n\nThe 5-fold CV results show NNs to outperform the remianing approaches whether the level of aggregation is at action level or at the student level.",
          "Amount of data required for the models to be effective is unclear.\n\nNeeds validation from additional datasets.\n\nResults obtained for this dataset are somewhat inconsistent with other results in the literature."
        ]
      ],
