    {
      "id": "18e4750c-f3ba-805c-b41c-e76ad4c657f1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Most of the previous KT models used have shown inconsistent results. They argue that, in large part, these inconsistencies come from dataset size. Thus, authors explore how enemble methods could perform on a large dataset. They compare the performance of 8 student models and 8 ensembles and see that the best ensemble outperforms the single models by close to 10 percentage points.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18e4750c-f3ba-805c-b41c-e76ad4c657f1",
